definitions.definition: An inhabitant of a place; one who dwells in a certain place.
examples: The giant squid is one of many denizens of the deep.
The denizens of that pub are of the roughest sort.

definitions.definition: A person with rights between those of naturalized citizen and resident alien (roughly permanent resident ), obtained through letters patent .
An animal or plant from a particular range or habitat .
examples: The bald eagle is a denizen of the northern part of the state.

definitions.definition: A foreign word that has become naturalised in another language in terms of use , but not in terms of form .
